";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Sun, 12 May 2019 06:07:22 PDT\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/database-caching-not-caching-queries-correctly/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2744:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>Hi everyone,</p>\n<p>Looks like Database caching is not working correctly in my WordPress installation. So, if I enable database caching, I get this:</p>\n<p>Database Caching 16/2588 queries in 1.411 seconds using memcache</p>\n<p>I enabled debugging &#8211; some queries have caching disabled, as expected, but most of them are like this:</p>\n<blockquote><p>   35 |   0.0004 |            enabled             | not cached |           593 |    options | SELECT option_value FROM wp_9pxazz_options WHERE option_name = &#8216;wp-optimize-logging&#8217; LIMIT 1<br />\n   36 |   0.0002 |            enabled             | not cached |           605 |    options | SELECT option_value FROM wp_9pxazz_options WHERE option_name = &#8216;wp-optimize-logging-additional&#8217; LIMIT 1<br />\n   37 |   0.0002 |            enabled             | not cached |           598 |    options | SELECT option_value FROM wp_9pxazz_options WHERE option_name = &#8216;wppfm_processed_products&#8217; LIMIT 1</p></blockquote>\n<p>For each of them caching is enabled, but the query is not cached;  if I refresh the page, I will see the exact same query, still not cached.</p>\n<p>Interesting is that I also saw this:</p>\n<blockquote><p>   55 |    0.001 |            enabled             | not cached |          4380 | singletables | SELECT * FROM wp_9pxazz_sfa_abandoned_carts WHERE customer_key = &#8216;&lt;redacted&gt;&#8217; AND cart_is_recovered = 0 AND order_id IS NULL LIMIT 1<br />\n   56 |   0.0002 |            enabled             |   cached   |          4405 | singletables | SELECT * FROM wp_9pxazz_sfa_abandoned_carts WHERE customer_key = &#8216;&lt;redacted_same_as_above&gt;&#8217; AND cart_is_recovered = 0 AND order_id IS NULL LIMIT 1</p></blockquote>\n<p>First time it was not cached, second time it was &#8212; maybe the cache doesn&#8217;t &#8220;stick&#8221; between page reloads? Maximum lifetime of cache objects is set to 86400s, and same is Garbage collection interval, so this shouldn&#8217;t be a problem.</p>\n<p>I tried changing the cache from memcached to disk, but I get very similar results &#8211; most queries are not cached.</p>\n<p>If I enable object caching as well, the number of queries go down a lot (expected), but most of them are still not cached:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Object Caching 3263/4204 objects using memcache<br />\nDatabase Caching 16/343 queries in 0.191 seconds using memcache</p></blockquote>\n<p>Using object caching does not seem to make the faster, though, maybe even a bit slower.</p>\n<p>Do you have any thoughts about what could be the cause or where else I could investigate?</p>\n<p>Thank you!</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/oZICSdVIMTQ\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"griggerr\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/database-caching-not-caching-queries-correctly/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:26;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"